# Default: LF in every working copy so hashes and locks are deterministic
# across Windows and Linux checkouts.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Raw authority artifacts are byte-exact by definition (framework spec §7.2).
# Git must never convert their line endings or otherwise touch their bytes —
# the LF/CRLF conversion channel is exactly the corruption that produced
# non-verbatim "verbatim" evidence in the failed prior attempt
# (WITNESSED-FAILURE-MODES.md #6). This rule is LAST because later
# gitattributes rules override earlier ones; placed before the catch-all it
# would be dead, which is precisely the defect CI caught on 2026-07-16
# (RAW_AUTHORITY_MUTATED on the CRLF ns-eel2 sources).
verification/authorities/raw/** -text
